<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT51.D4.SD3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subdivision" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBDIVISION" subdoc="false" toc-caption="Subdivision 3 Powers on applications for leave [rr 51.14, 51.15]">
<leg:heading><desig searchtype="SUBDIV-NUM"><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT51.D4.SD3" type="ext"/>Subdivision 3</designum></desig><title searchtype="SUBDIV-TITLE">Powers on applications for leave [rr 51.14, 51.15]</title></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-14"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[r 51.14] r 51.14 Concurrent hearings in relation to leave applications">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-14" type="ext"/>[r 51.14]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Concurrent hearings in relation to leave applications</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>51.14</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-14.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-14.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The Court may deal with applications for the following orders in the absence of the public and without the attendance of any person:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-14.1.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-14.1.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>an order that 2 or more applications for leave to appeal or cross-appeal be heard concurrently,</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-14.1.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-14.1.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>an order that an application for leave to appeal or cross-appeal be heard concurrently with the argument on the appeal or cross-appeal.</text></p>
</li>
</l>
<glp:note>
<heading><title>Note.</title></heading>
<p>
<text><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="SCPNSW.SCN.SCA70.S46" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID" status="unval">Section 46</remotelink>
 of the Supreme Court Act 1970 provides that a single Judge of Appeal may exercise the powers of the Court to make an order or give any direction concerning the institution of an appeal or other proceedings in the Court.</text></p></glp:note>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-14.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-14.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>If the Court makes an order under subrule (1)(b), the parties must, within 28 days (but subject to any directions given by the Court), cause any necessary additional documents to be added to the White Folder.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:bodytext>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTES"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT51.R14.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTES</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_UCPR.SGM_UCPN.UCPR.51-14-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[51.14.5] Concurrent hearings"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.51-14-5" type="ext"/>[51.14.5] </edpnum><title>Concurrent hearings</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>Each party&#x2019;s summary of argument should indicate whether it is appropriate to have a concurrent hearing of the leave application and the substantive appeal. The argument should address (i) the extent of commonality between the leave and appeal issues, (ii) any issue of public importance is involved, (iii) any prejudice apprehended to be caused by separate hearings, and (iv) any specific reason why leave is required in the particular circumstances: see Practice Note SC CA 1 at [19]. </text></p>
<p>
<text>A direction for concurrent hearing of an application for leave, and the substantive appeal, is a matter for the court&#x2019;s discretion. It requires neither an application by, nor the consent of, the parties: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="2010"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr011507" spanref="cr011507-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="79"/><ci:page num="354"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr011508" spanref="cr011508-002"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC201002150"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Avery v Registrar of Births, Deaths and Marriages; Avery v New South Wales (Attorney General's Department)</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr011507-001">(2010) 79 NSWLR 354</ci:span>; [2010] NSWCA 72; <ci:span spanid="cr011508-002"> BC201002150</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="492611" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr011509" spanref="cr011509-000"><ci:reporter value="NSWCA"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="2010"/></ci:edition><ci:pinpoint num="160" targettype="para"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"><ci:span spanid="cr011509-000">at [160]</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> per Campbell JA. A direction for a concurrent hearing will be appropriate where the court is satisfied of at least one of the following matters: </text>
<l>
<li>
<lilabel>(i)</lilabel>
<p><text>the probability that leave will be granted;</text></p></li>
<li>
<lilabel>(ii)</lilabel>
<p><text>there is substantial commonality of facts and issues between the leave application and the substantive appeal;</text></p></li>
<li>
<lilabel>(iii)</lilabel>
<p><text>the amount in issue approximates the threshold value (where the leave requirement arises from a value threshold): right to appeal is subject to a value threshold: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr011510" spanref="cr011510-001"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC201003726"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Agricultural and Rural Finance Pty Ltd v Kirk</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> [2010] NSWCA 132; <ci:span spanid="cr011510-001"> BC201003726</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="496468" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr011511" spanref="cr011511-000" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="NSWCA"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="2010"/></ci:edition><ci:pinpoint num="10" targettype="para"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"><ci:span spanid="cr011511-000" status="unval">at [10]</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> per Basten JA;</text></p></li>
<li>
<lilabel>(iv)</lilabel>
<p><text>the substantive appeal hearing is unlikely to require hearing time additional to that required by the leave application: balance of convenience.</text></p></li></l></p>
<p>
<text>See <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr011512" spanref="cr011512-001"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC201203956"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr011512" spanref="cr011512-002"><ci:pinpoint num="40" targettype="para"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Be Financial Pty Ltd v Das</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> [2012] NSWCA 164; <ci:span spanid="cr011512-001"> BC201203956</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr011512-002">at [40]</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="554149" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_UCPR.SGM_UCPN.UCPR.51-14-6" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[51.14.6] Concurrent hearings &#x2014; &#x201c;white folder&#x201d; contents"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.51-14-6" type="ext"/>[51.14.6] </edpnum><title>Concurrent hearings &#x2014; &#x201c;white folder&#x201d; contents</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>Where an order for concurrent hearing is made, the parties must file a chronology and provide any additional submissions (or notice that none is to be provided) in the form and within the times required by UCPR r 51.39A. In order to comply with those requirements, the adequacy of the contents of the white folder should be reviewed to ensure it contains all the submissions and material &#x201c;necessary&#x201d; for the efficient conduct of the substantive appeal. The submissions included in the white folder should be of the same standard as those expected of any appellant: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="2007"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr011513" spanref="cr011513-001"><ci:reporter value="MVR"/><ci:volume num="48"/><ci:page num="136"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr011514" spanref="cr011514-002"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC200703074"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr011514" spanref="cr011514-003"><ci:pinpoint num="65" targettype="para"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Hooker v Gilling</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr011513-001">(2007) 48 MVR 136</ci:span>; [2007] NSWCA 99; <ci:span spanid="cr011514-002"> BC200703074</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr011514-003">at [65]&#x2013;[67]</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="436227" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> per McColl JA (citing <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">MacDonald v Martin</emph></citefragment>, <emph typestyle="it">above</emph></ci:content></ci:cite> at [38]). </text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-15"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[r 51.15] r 51.15 Court may determine application for leave without attendance (cf SCR Part 51, rule 4D)">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-15" type="ext"/>[r 51.15]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Court may determine application for leave without attendance (cf SCR Part 51, rule 4D)</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>51.15</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>An application for leave to appeal or to cross-appeal may be dealt with by the Court in the absence of the public and without the attendance of any person if:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-15..A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-15..A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>the application is not opposed, or</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-15..B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-15..B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>each active party consents.</text></p>
</li>
</l>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level></leg:levelbody></leg:level-vrnt></leg:level></leg:levelbody></leg:level-vrnt></leg:level></leg:body></LEGDOC>